Las Vegas, located in Clark Count has an estimated 800,000 people
living there out of 1.3 million people in Nevada.  That gives Clark
county control in the state Legislature since they have 63 of the 99
seats.  Three counties with only 35,000 people are fighting the Las
Vegas water plan with little chance to win.

Las Vegas is holding another ace up its sleeve since Clark county
Casinos provide for 70 percent of the state's gaming revenues.
Basically, whatever Clark County wants Clark County gets.  Other
counties hope they don't go down the drain if Clark County mishandles
the water law.  </SUM>

<SUM
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP890623-0230"
SELECTOR="D"
SUMMARIZER="D"> 

Japanese investors and tourists are fueling an economic boom in Las
Vegas, spending or committing over $800 million dollars.  Yoshi
Morichika is heading up a 1,270 acre golf and destination resort
community for Japanese recreation and electronics giant Cosmo World in
nearby Henderson at a cost of $200 million.

Japanese businessman Katsuki Manabe has invested $30 million in the
Park Hotel in downtown Las Vegas and millions more in his Nevada-based
Sigma Games, which makes gaming equipment.

However, some Japanese investors are running into financial difficulty
with their investments and failing properties such as the Dunes and
the Aladdin hotels.  </SUM>

<SUM
TYPE="PERDOC"
